# Streamlit UI (`app.py`, `ui/`)

## Boundaries

- **`app.py`**: orchestration only — session state, uploads, wiring to `ui/*` and `ReportEngine`. No merge logic that belongs in `engine.py`.
- **Never add `import streamlit` to `engine.py`** — merge core stays headless for CLI, tests, and Power Automate.

## Module roles (see [docs/05-developer-guide.md](docs/05-developer-guide.md))

| Module | Responsibility |
|--------|----------------|
| `ui/sidebar.py` | Profile, phase sync, meta, executive override, sample downloads |
| `ui/phrase_panel.py` | Standard phrases selectboxes → `phrase_meta` merged into render meta |
| `ui/helpers.py` | Template cache, PDF→DOCX path, sample ensure |
| `ui/preflight.py` | Cached preflight, SED 002 §10 metrics, appendix-aware checklist, ReportConfig export |
| `ui/preview.py` | Dry-run panel |
| `ui/results.py` | Single-report downloads; `render_batch_download_section` for batch zip |
| `ui/appendix_panel.py` | Appendices A–H, deliverable zip (incl. OneStop export) |
| `ui/ai_panel.py` | Optional AI tab (offline fallbacks in `ai/`) |
| `ui/workflow_mode.py` | Startup picker: project folder + AI vs Excel + template upload |
| `ui/project_folder.py` | Project folder path loader and meta merge |
| `ui/folder_picker.py` | Native OS folder dialog (local desktop Browse button) |
| `ai/source_ingest.py` | Ingest `source/` PDFs → `ai_drafts/` summaries for narratives |

## Batch mode

When `ProjectData` has more than one data row, `app.py` offers **Single report** vs **All N reports (batch)**. Batch calls `ReportEngine.render_batch()` and stores results in `session_state.generated_batch` for `render_batch_download_section`.

## UX rules

- On launch, users **choose a workflow** (`ui/workflow_mode.py`): project folder + AI or Excel + template upload.
- Persist **generated bytes and manifest** in **session state** so download survives reruns.
- **Widget session keys** — never assign `st.session_state.<widget_key>` after that widget is drawn (Streamlit raises `StreamlitAPIException`). Set pending values before the widget (e.g. `project_folder_path_pending` → assign `project_folder_path_input` at top of `_render_folder_controls`).
- Surface **user-safe** errors from `security.user_safe_error`; do not leak raw tracebacks for uploads.
